            id="tab-is"
            class="ez-tab text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold pb-3 border-b-4 border-black dark:border-white text-black dark:text-white transition-all"
            data-tab="is"
          >
            What EZ is
          </button>
          <button
            id="tab-is-not"
            class="ez-tab text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold pb-3 border-b-4 border-transparent text-black dark:text-white opacity-40 hover:opacity-70 transition-all"
            data-tab="is-not"
          >
            What EZ is not
          </button>
        </div>

        <!-- Content Container -->
        <div class="relative overflow-hidden">
          <div id="slider" class="flex transition-transform duration-300 ease-in-out">
            <!-- What EZ Is Content -->
            <div class="min-w-full px-4">
              <ul class="space-y-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-lg sm:text-xl leading-relaxed text-black dark:text-white">
                <li>
                  <strong>Simple, not shallow</strong> &mdash; clean syntax that scales with your skill.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Explicit by design</strong> &mdash; nothing happens behind your back. You control what the code does.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Catch mistakes before you run</strong> &mdash; types are checked before execution, so errors don't surprise you later.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Procedural and functional</strong> &mdash; simple data + functions. Composition over abstraction.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Error messages that teach</strong> &mdash; clear, detailed formatting that tells you what happened, where, why, and how to fix it.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- What EZ Is Not Content -->
            <div class="min-w-full px-4">
              <ul class="space-y-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-lg sm:text-xl leading-relaxed text-black dark:text-white">
                <li>
                  <strong>A copycat</strong> &mdash; not chasing trends, not competing with the big names.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Object-oriented</strong> &mdash; no classes, no objects, no inheritance. Ever.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>A toy</strong> &mdash; simple doesn't mean limited. You can build real things with it.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Guessing what you meant</strong> &mdash; it does what you write, not what it thinks you wanted.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Trying to be everything</strong> &mdash; focused scope. Every feature earns its place.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
